  "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\n`eth2ResponseTimer` is where we handle TTFB_TIMEOUT and RESP_TIMEOUT but it doesn't throw error at the right time\r\n\r\n```\r\n2020-10-21 12:07:05 [NETWORK]       ^[[36mverbose^[[39m: sending beacon_blocks_by_range request to 16Uiu2HAmQRvkQZcF8enhAiUC7rnzrooYbqRmU5hSRKkPyYufwobZ requestId=0920a136136769b4, encoding=ssz_snappy\r\n2020-10-21 12:07:19 [NETWORK]       ^[[36mverbose^[[39m: got stream to 16Uiu2HAmQRvkQZcF8enhAiUC7rnzrooYbqRmU5hSRKkPyYufwobZ requestId=0920a136136769b4, encoding=ssz_snappy\r\n2020-10-21 12:21:32 [NETWORK]       ^[[36mverbose^[[39m: peer disconnected 16Uiu2HAmQRvkQZcF8enhAiUC7rnzrooYbqRmU5hSRKkPyYufwobZ\r\n2020-10-21 12:21:32 [NETWORK]          ^[[33mwarn^[[39m: failed to send request 0920a136136769b4 to peer 16Uiu2HAmQRvkQZcF8enhAiUC7rnzrooYbqRmU5hSRKkPyYufwobZ method=beacon_blocks_by_range, reason=response timeout\r\n``` \r\nin fact it only throws error at the time the peer is disconnected and our sync has to wait for 14 minutes. I got same issue with another peer in my log as well.\r\n\r\nWe may have to wait longer if peer is disconnected after hours.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\neth2ResponseTimer throws error after RESP_TIMEOUT which is 10s",
